STEP-BY-STEP SETUP
STEP 1 — Create replication user on Production

Login:

docker exec -it passbolt-db-CHOC mariadb -uroot -p

Run:

CREATE USER 'repl'@'10.22.105.16' IDENTIFIED BY 'StrongReplicationPass';

GRANT REPLICATION SLAVE ON *.* TO 'repl'@'10.22.105.16';

FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
STEP 2 — Take Initial Backup
docker exec passbolt-db-CHOC \
mysqldump -uroot -p \
--all-databases \
--single-transaction \
--master-data=2 \
> full_backup.sql
STEP 3 — Restore to DR

Copy to DR server and run:

docker exec -i passbolt-db-DR \
mariadb -uroot -p < full_backup.sql
STEP 4 — Configure Replication

Login DR:

docker exec -it passbolt-db-DR mariadb -uroot -p

Run:

CHANGE MASTER TO
MASTER_HOST='10.112.160.197',
MASTER_USER='repl',
MASTER_PASSWORD='StrongReplicationPass',
MASTER_USE_GTID=slave_pos;

START SLAVE;
STEP 5 — Verify
SHOW SLAVE STATUS\G

Must show:

Slave_IO_Running: Yes
Slave_SQL_Running: Yes
